1.title: Anti-Borings
1.plot: Did you hear that Jess was diagnosed as being boring? At least she's taking those anti-boring pills.

2.title: Therapy
2.plot: Did you hear they had an intervention for Jess? Maybe she'll finally get the help she needs.

3.title: Dating
3.plot: Did you hear Jess is finally getting out there and seeing people? I hope she finds the one.

4.title: Routine
4.plot: Did you hear Jess has Henry Hénry as her personal life coach? He's so amazing.

5.title: Starting Over
5.plot: Did you hear Jess is moving? Starting fresh will be good for her.

imdb.plot outline: Diagnosis: Boring is a web series that tackles the intricacies of struggling with modern day depression in an exaggerated, surrealist version of our world. The series follows Jess Lowry, a prototypical millennial after she is diagnosed with a fatal case of being "boring", an allegory for depression in our world. Jess finds herself in a position that many people today find themselves in: socially connected, employed, healthy, and utterly miserable. We watch as, episode by episode, Jess goes through everyday cures for being boring-therapy apps, self-help gurus, reliance on alcohol. The story of Jess Lowry is very much one of a sane character in an insane world. The trickiness of depression is that it tends to be a sickness that affects the patients logic, and people suffering from it often don't feel like there is anything wrong with them, but rather the world around them. Diagnosis: Boring aims to get in Jess's head, to a place where the viewing audience can see things the same way she does.

plot: _Diagnosis: Boring_ (qv) follows Jess Lowry, the prototypical millennial, whose life is thrown into a tailspin when her doctor diagnoses her with a potentially fatal case of being boring.::Michael Schiff
